<speak version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US">
  <voice name="en-US-AriaNeural">
    <prosody rate="-20%" pitch="-8%" volume="-5%">
      <!-- THE CLEARING — CINEMATIC AUDIO DRAMA -->

      <break time="1s"/>
      You close the door behind you... for the last time.
      The key turns... you don't leave it on the counter.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      There are no letters. No explanations.
      Some people... don't deserve them.
      <break time="1s"/>

      Your car waits. Old. Reliable. Already packed.
      Engine starts... radio crackles... you turn it off.
      <break time="1s"/>
      The highway stretches—monotonous... hypnotic.
      The city shrinks to a smudge in the mirror.
      <break time="2s"/>

      A rest stop. Late light. Fewer cars.
      An older woman steps closer.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      You alright, honey? You look like you're saying goodbye to something.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      I am.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      The right kind of goodbye... or the wrong kind?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Still figuring that out.
      <break time="1s"/>
      The road tells you things... if you let it.
      Heading anywhere specific?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Away. Toward quiet.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Quiet's hard to find. But it's out there... in the spaces between things.
      <break time="1s"/>
      Safe travels.
      <break time="2s"/>

      Weeks pass. Maybe two months. Maybe three.
      You leave the car in a small town—keys on the seat, a note:
      Use it if you need it.
      <break time="1s"/>
      Boots on dry earth. Breath steady. Hands roughened. Skin knows sun and wind.
      <break time="1.2s"/>

      At a cold stream. Water tastes like stone and time.
      A branch snaps. A voice appears.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Water's clean here. Upstream from the road. You're doing it right.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      How far is the nearest road?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Depends where you're trying to go.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Away from roads.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Then you're going the right direction.
      <break time="1s"/>
      How long you been out?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Time's different here.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Took me a month to stop counting days. Another to stop counting weeks.
      After that... you stop measuring by what you left behind.
      <break time="1.5s"/>
      There's a cabin four miles north. Hunters use it. Hold up for the winter.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Why help me?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Someone helped me once. And I remember not knowing if I was running toward something... or away from it.
      Doesn't matter much. You end up in the same place either way.
      <break time="2s"/>

      Storm night in the cabin. Rain on tin. Thunder distant.
      A journal of voices:
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Day forty-seven. I've stopped hearing the phones. While I'm awake... it's quiet. The quiet of arrival.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      I don't know who I am anymore... but that might be okay.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      My mother would hate this. My father would call it irresponsible. I'm happier than I've ever been.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Day sixty-eight. I remembered who I am... when there was no one to remember me for.
      <break time="2s"/>

      Dawn. High ridge. Endless view.
      A young woman watches the sunrise.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      First time at this altitude?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      What makes you think that?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      You're crying.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      It's a lot to take in.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      It gets smaller every time you come back. But the first time... breaks your heart open.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      I come here when doubt gets loud.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Does it?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Every few weeks. I think about hot showers. Pizza delivery. People who knew my name.
      Then I remember I hated all of it. I was dying slowly in a room with all the lights on.
      <break time="2s"/>
      Stay to watch the light change... three times. That's when you know you're really here.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Where are you going?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Higher.
      <break time="2s"/>

      A year since you left the city. It was a place. You were simply in it.
      Now you are... remade.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      A clearing. Air feels taller. Space opens.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      An elder with kind eyes arrives.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Thought I might find you here.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      How did you know this place?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Thirty years at a desk before I realized I was dying sitting down.
      I came to a clearing like this. Took me five years to understand what I was looking at.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      What were you looking at?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Everything I'd missed. Everything waiting.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      I'm not here to pull you back. Not to say you were wrong.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Then why?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      To tell you it's okay to leave. And it's okay to return.
      The courage isn't in escaping. It's in finding out who you are... and then choosing.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      I'm going back tomorrow. Grandkids I haven't met. A life half-lived—I'm going to start living.
      Needed to come here first. To remember I was alive once.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      You're leaving?
      <break time="600ms"/>
      Yeah. But I'm not running. I'm choosing. That's the difference.
      <break time="2s"/>

      Silence. The clearing holds you.
      Voices of those you met... faint, like echoes:
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Same place either way...
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Dying slowly in a room with all the lights on...
      <break time="800ms"/>
      The road tells you things if you let it...
      <break time="800ms"/>
      Finding out who you are...
      <break time="2s"/>

      You sit through the night. Not meditating. Just sitting.
      Something tight in your chest... releases.
      Breath deepens. Matches the wind. Becomes part of this place.
      <break time="1.5s"/>
      You didn't leave to escape them. You left to find you.
      You did. You're whole. Not complete—nothing is—but whole enough to carry.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      You stand.
      <break time="600ms"/>
      I'm ready.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      Not ready to flee. Ready for what comes.
      <break time="1.2s"/>

      The clearing is a threshold. Forest behind. Trail ahead. Towns. People. The world.
      Your hand skims the tall grass as you walk. Every choice is written in your body now.
      You cannot forget who you are.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      Sunlight warms the soundscape.
      You step out. Trees close gently behind. You are not leaving paradise. You are bringing it with you.
      <break time="1.5s"/>

      A road down the mountain. A bus on Thursdays.
      You have time. To walk. To integrate. To return as someone who knows themselves.
      <break time="1.2s"/>
      Boots on earth. Steady. Unhurried.
      <break time="800ms"/>
      You were brave enough to leave.
      Strong enough to survive.
      Now wise enough to return—not escaping, but choosing.
      <break time="2s"/>

      That's the clearing's gift.
      Not escape.
      A mirror.
      You saw yourself. Clearly.
      And now... you can take that clarity anywhere.
      <break time="3s"/>

    </prosody>
  </voice>
</speak>
